{"sections":[{"kind":"hero","xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 26.4","image":"ic_unified_ds.png","estimatedTimeInMinutes":10,"title":"Swift Package integration","chapter":"Import of the Swift Package and choose its librairies","projectFiles":"OUDS-Onboarding-Tutorial.zip","backgroundImage":"ic_unified_ds.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS iOS is exposed through an open source Swift Package hosted on GitHub, and provides several librairies for your needs."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"These librairies help to split products and make users able to select only what they need."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI is the only official supported framework for Apple platforms."}]}]},{"tasks":[{"contentSection":[{"kind":"contentAndMedia","mediaPosition":"trailing","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS for iOS is an open source Swift Package available on GitHub under MIT license.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The package and the librairies must be added through Xcode."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"title":"Import the Swift Package and the libraries","stepsSection":[{"type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Using Xcode, in your ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"project package dependencies","type":"text"}]},{"text":", add a new ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"dependency"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Search with the GitHub repository URL (https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios), and select the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ouds-ios"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" dependency.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can then choose the ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"dependency rule","type":"text"}]},{"text":" you want.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To know which version you need, you can have a look on the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/wiki\/01-%E2%80%90-Available-API","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and also the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/releases","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"runtimePreview":null,"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s say you will use the some beta version, here 1.3.0-beta.2"}]}],"code":null,"media":"tutorial-onboarding-1-ouds-swift-package.png"},{"code":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add for example only the umbrella product merging all products mentioned above: "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":"tutorial-onboarding-1-ouds-libraries.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Once you downloaded the package, you will see several librairies are available.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"They can be embeded inside your ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"target","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" librairies."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Things are separated to let users integrate only what they need and embed the abre minimum of content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesContract","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" library provides the main elements like the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSThemeableView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The theme contract is defined inside it.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesOrange"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesSosh"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Sosh products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesWireframe"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Wireframe theme, which is a theme dedicated to mockups and prototypes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesOrangeCompact"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products but with constraints of sizes and spaces.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSComponents","type":"text"}]},{"text":" contains the SwiftUI OUDS components defined with the Figma specifications, and also useful view modifers.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensRaw","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensSemantic"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensComponents","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are librairies defining and providing the tokens for low level (raw),"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"middle level (semantic) or component levels (high level).","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSModules","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is for modules or rich components with extra logic."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSFoundations"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" is dedicated to some utilities and shared logic."}]}],"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step"}],"anchor":"Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries"}],"kind":"tasks"},{"kind":"assessments","assessments":[{"choices":[{"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS is open source, under MIT license, and hosted on GitHub. Of course you can contribute!"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"I can contribute to OUDS using pull request"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS supports officialy all Apple OS like visionOS, tvOS, watchOS, iPadOS, iOS and also CarPlay.","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The main supported targets are iOS \/ iPadOS. However we do our best to support macOS, visionOS, tvOS and watchOS."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"CarPlay specific cases are not scoped yet."}]}]},{"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS supports only SwiftUI."}]}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS provides UIKit components"}]}],"isCorrect":false}],"title":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Which of these choices is correct?"}]}],"type":"multiple-choice","content":[]},{"type":"multiple-choice","title":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Which imports of the OUDS Swift Package products can I choose?","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"choices":[{"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can import all products provided by the Swift Package, and tailor your choice to keep only the ones needed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Even if we recommend to choose only the atomic products you need, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" product wraps all of them."}]}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some of the available products depending to my needs, or only "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSSwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" if I am very lazy and don’t care about my app size."}]}]},{"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You need to chose the products the Swift package provides.","type":"text"}]}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"None, only the Swift package dependency matter.","type":"text"}]}]}],"content":[]}],"anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding"},{"title":"Define information cards","action":{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Get started","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-2-nice-and-clear-view"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s suppose we want to define a view for corporate apps with headings, texts, buttons and images."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"How can we do that?"}],"featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial","kind":"callToAction"}],"hierarchy":{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)","paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)","doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)\/$volume","doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)\/Import-of-the-Swift-Package-and-choose-its-librairies"]],"modules":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(onboarding)\/Import-of-the-Swift-Package-and-choose-its-librairies","projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-1-package-and-librairies","sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries"},{"kind":"assessment","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-onboarding-1-pack